WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:06.280
So I'll try to provide an overview and considering the time limitations, I'll just really highlight

00:00:06.280 --> 00:00:11.320
some of the data that came from ASH this year and also kind of the areas that we need a

00:00:11.320 --> 00:00:13.360
lot of improvement on.

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:16.900
I shared the excitement that my myeloma colleagues had this morning.

00:00:16.900 --> 00:00:19.860
We have a lot more work to do, I think, in diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.

00:00:19.860 --> 00:00:24.320
So this is the current paradigm for treatment and management of diffuse large B-cell lymphoma.

00:00:24.320 --> 00:00:27.160
This is adapted from the NCCN guidelines.

00:00:27.160 --> 00:00:31.400
In the frontline setting, the anthracycline-based therapies have an established role in the

00:00:31.400 --> 00:00:40.440
more recent data set that was updated with Polarix's five-year follow-up, establishing

00:00:40.440 --> 00:00:45.960
improved efficacy in favor of a polituzumab anthracycline-based backbone.

00:00:45.960 --> 00:00:50.780
And you can see on the left upper-hand side, the panel there, the curves still persist.

00:00:50.780 --> 00:00:53.440
So the responses continue to persist.

00:00:53.440 --> 00:00:56.880
And on the right-hand side in the panel, you can see...

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:56.880
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:56.880 --> 00:00:56.920
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:56.920 --> 00:00:56.960
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:56.960 --> 00:00:57.020
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:57.020 --> 00:00:57.120
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:57.120 --> 00:00:57.140
Even though the cell lymphomas are still present, the response continues to persist.

00:00:57.160 --> 00:00:59.100
The study didn't have an overall survival benefit.

00:00:59.360 --> 00:01:04.360
There is an advantage to the progression-free survival in the sense that a lot of the patients

00:01:04.360 --> 00:01:10.160
require less subsequent lines of therapy in terms of systemic therapy, transplant, CAR-T

00:01:10.160 --> 00:01:11.360
cells, or radiotherapy.

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:17.640
And this was a very, very tolerable regimen, and most patients can complete their therapy.

00:01:17.960 --> 00:01:20.580
Now, what else is remaining in the frontline setting?

00:01:20.700 --> 00:01:22.100
Obviously, we're not curing everybody.

00:01:22.380 --> 00:01:27.060
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:27.240
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.240 --> 00:01:27.260
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.260 --> 00:01:27.280
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:27.320
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.320 --> 00:01:27.360
So part of the problem still remains increasing response.

00:01:27.360 --> 00:01:31.400
And increasing durable responses and cures in the frontline setting.

00:01:31.740 --> 00:01:33.400
And specifically, who am I talking about?

00:01:33.760 --> 00:01:40.300
Patients that have high-risk IPI and molecularly high-risk disease, double hits, triple hits,

00:01:40.460 --> 00:01:41.520
those kinds of things.

00:01:41.660 --> 00:01:47.500
And so in this context, there is some thought of incorporating, obviously, new agents, including

00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:53.820
bispecifics in frontline, as well as including other targeted agents like BTK inhibitors in

00:01:53.820 --> 00:01:54.240
the frontline.

00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:57.080
Some of the newer data, and this is what I'm highlighting here.

00:01:57.080 --> 00:02:04.020
There is, regarding autologous CAR-T-cells, CD19-directed CAR-T-cells, there were a number

00:02:04.020 --> 00:02:05.260
of abstracts in this regard.

00:02:05.600 --> 00:02:07.020
And this is a representative one.

00:02:07.380 --> 00:02:11.860
This is RAP-captogen, a CD19-directed CAR.

00:02:12.540 --> 00:02:16.720
This study was for frontline treatment of patients.

00:02:17.180 --> 00:02:24.100
And on the bottom left-hand corner of the screen, you can see this is majority of the

00:02:24.100 --> 00:02:25.920
patients have high risk by IPI.

00:02:27.040 --> 00:02:32.740
In the middle column there, you can see with frontline use, overall response rate here

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:37.220
was 90%, with 74% of these patients achieving a complete response.

00:02:37.340 --> 00:02:40.760
So at least in this context, we are able to control the disease.

00:02:41.100 --> 00:02:45.900
This is a short-term, the follow-up was relatively short on this study.

00:02:46.300 --> 00:02:52.640
So at least in the context of this presentation, the median duration of response was not reached.

00:02:53.380 --> 00:02:56.640
At six months, about 80% of the patients still remain.

00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:59.780
Free of disease.

00:03:00.180 --> 00:03:05.400
And so at least it lends itself to the possibility that we can use this strategy in frontline

00:03:05.400 --> 00:03:06.740
for high-risk patients.

00:03:07.320 --> 00:03:13.980
The other thing to think about is, does everybody really need aggressive cytotoxic chemotherapy?

00:03:14.600 --> 00:03:20.780
There were, as a study done in 2019, this has been publicized with mosonatuzumab in elderly

00:03:20.780 --> 00:03:25.320
patients that are ineligible for anthracycline-based therapy.

00:03:25.320 --> 00:03:26.960
And in that category of patients, we have a lot of patients who are ineligible for anthracycline-based

00:03:26.960 --> 00:03:27.200
therapy.

00:03:27.200 --> 00:03:31.020
And in that category of patients, about 30% of the patients actually remained free of

00:03:31.020 --> 00:03:35.700
disease with just frontline bispecific therapy.

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:38.900
This is, they never got any chemotherapy, any sort of cytotoxic.

00:03:38.980 --> 00:03:40.400
So that's the old data.

00:03:40.760 --> 00:03:47.740
And this is from a separate study Jeff Sharman presented this year at ASH, reflecting essentially

00:03:47.740 --> 00:03:48.280
the same thing.

00:03:48.280 --> 00:03:55.780
The Morning Sun study was a large study, and they reported a DLBC health cohort here for

00:03:55.780 --> 00:03:56.920
elderly patients that are...

00:03:56.920 --> 00:03:59.260
Or patients that have comorbidities that are ineligible.

00:03:59.740 --> 00:04:03.880
And on the bottom left-hand side, you can see the overall response rate here, again,

00:04:03.880 --> 00:04:09.140
with single-agent mosonatuzumab with large-cell lymphoma, overall response rate is around

00:04:09.140 --> 00:04:10.020
70%.

00:04:10.020 --> 00:04:13.020
Majority of that tends to be a CR.

00:04:14.140 --> 00:04:18.420
And again, with a very short follow-up on the bottom right-hand side, you can see there

00:04:18.420 --> 00:04:18.880
are...

00:04:18.880 --> 00:04:20.240
This is extremely short follow-up.

00:04:20.360 --> 00:04:26.360
So I think the majority of the data in this regard would come from older studies and observing

00:04:26.360 --> 00:04:26.880
these patients.

00:04:26.880 --> 00:04:27.300
I think the majority of the data is from older studies and observing these patients for a

00:04:27.300 --> 00:04:27.600
long term.

00:04:27.600 --> 00:04:35.600
But it proves the point that potentially some patients may not need cytotoxic chemotherapy

00:04:35.600 --> 00:04:39.780
for treatment of their diffuse large B-cell lymphoma, especially in the context of these

00:04:39.780 --> 00:04:43.660
previously untreated patients that actually have an intact immune system.

00:04:44.920 --> 00:04:49.640
This is a similar study with epcortimab, same patient population, but I highlighted there

00:04:49.640 --> 00:04:56.420
at the bottom middle panel there, on this particular study, again, same strategy of

00:04:56.420 --> 00:05:01.240
epcortimab, a CD20 bispecific as single-agent.

00:05:02.240 --> 00:05:07.640
This study actually evaluated MRD, and you can see in the bottom middle column there

00:05:07.640 --> 00:05:12.740
with single-agent epcortimab, you can actually achieve MRD negativity and sustain it.

00:05:12.740 --> 00:05:19.880
Again, a very short follow-up requires longer follow-up, but same concept can be re-emphasized.

00:05:19.960 --> 00:05:23.800
Now, in the relapsed refractory setting, we have quite a number of options in terms of

00:05:23.800 --> 00:05:26.060
CAR-T-cells bispecific.

00:05:26.380 --> 00:05:29.620
So, you can see that there are two combinations, and polituzumab combinations, and the same thing

00:05:29.620 --> 00:05:30.900
applies in the third-line setting.

